# UI product sync

Apply when editing front-end UI, design docs, or Tailwind/theme tokens.

---

## Before any UI work

Read in order:

1. [PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md](../../claude-design-docs/PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md) — **canonical hierarchy + flow summary**
2. [BORDERLESS-THEMING.md](../../claude-design-docs/BORDERLESS-THEMING.md) — **canonical Borderless visual language** (tokens, shell, canvas, nodes)
3. [UX-FLOW.md](../../claude-design-docs/UX-FLOW.md) — screen-by-screen flow (HAC-21+)
4. [SCREEN-INTENT.md](../../claude-design-docs/SCREEN-INTENT.md) — per-screen must-match
5. [UI-PRINCIPLES.md](../../claude-design-docs/UI-PRINCIPLES.md)
6. [references/borderless-code-breakers-dashboard.png](../../claude-design-docs/references/borderless-code-breakers-dashboard.png) — steady-state shell + canvas (primary)
7. [references/borderless-logo-brand.png](../../claude-design-docs/references/borderless-logo-brand.png) — brand colors
8. Target screen components in [`claude-design-docs/prototype/`](../../claude-design-docs/prototype/) (tokens only — flow may lag)
9. [docs/CHECKPOINT.md](../../docs/CHECKPOINT.md) — P0 scope + demo script
10. [UI-SUGGESTIONS-BACKLOG.md](../../claude-design-docs/UI-SUGGESTIONS-BACKLOG.md) — pending user UI feedback

Compare three views:

- **Docs intent** — UX-FLOW + SCREEN-INTENT (wins over prototype flow)
- **Prototype** — tokens, components, copy
- **Implemented UI** — `apps/frontend/` when present
- **Product goals** — CHECKPOINT wow features

Resolve conflicts using the hierarchy in PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH (goals → screen intent → prototype → code).

---

## After UI sessions — update canonical docs

If the session changed **UI paradigm**, update docs in the **same session** (before ending):

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| New/changed route or flow | [UX-FLOW.md](../../claude-design-docs/UX-FLOW.md) + [SCREEN-INTENT.md](../../claude-design-docs/SCREEN-INTENT.md) + [SCREEN-INTENT-MAP.md](../../claude-design-docs/SCREEN-INTENT-MAP.md) |
| Token / color / typography / theming | [design-tokens.md](../../claude-design-docs/design-tokens.md) + [BORDERLESS-THEMING.md](../../claude-design-docs/BORDERLESS-THEMING.md) |
| Deliberate prototype divergence | [PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md](../../claude-design-docs/PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH.md) → Implementation notes |
| New shared component pattern | PRODUCT-SOURCE-OF-TRUTH Implementation notes + UI-PRINCIPLES component table |

**UI paradigm change** means any of:

- New reusable component pattern
- Layout shift (forge timeline-only, vertical roadmap, sidebar)
- Design token change
- New screen or altered navigation flow
- Status UX or roadmap interaction change

Skill for explicit sync: [.cursor/skills/ui-product-sync/SKILL.md](../skills/ui-product-sync/SKILL.md)

---

## Do not

- Ship UI that weakens P0 wow (Forge timeline stream, animation reveal, validation, adaptive roadmap) without CHECKPOINT update
- Show skill graph during forge stream (HAC-21 — timeline only)
- Use read-only diagnosis confirmation dead-end (HAC-21 — editable diagnosis + "Gerar roadmap")
- Introduce gamification / LMS patterns rejected in UI-PRINCIPLES
- Rename skill status enums without API + CHECKPOINT alignment

